The Vice President, alongside other government officials and honored guests, spoke at the National D-Day Memorial in Bedford, Virginia to commemorate the 75th anniversary of D-Day. He expressed gratitude and admiration for the veterans of that historic day, acknowledging their bravery and sacrifice. He also paid tribute to the Bedford Boys, a group of soldiers from Bedford who fought and died on Omaha Beach. The Vice President emphasized that the true memorial to these heroes is the freedom they fought to defend. He concluded by thanking the veterans for their service and reaffirming the nation's commitment to honoring their sacrifice.